cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on neural networks and their approximation capabilities, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization-based design, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of logarithmic activation functions and log-convex sets suggests a connection to cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.SY (Control and Optimization).
